Well, I have no clue about planes, but I have been on and led a few dungeon raids. Now these have been guild raids only, and each guild does things differently. How our looting rules have been done is each group has a master looter who loots everything that group kills, except for no drops which are roled on then and there. After the raid, we announce what has been looted and let everyone roll. Need before greed is our main rule. If the character you brought on your raid can and will use the item, they get to roll. Then they're out of any other rolls unless it's an item no one else can use. For example, we raided Najena and had a LOT of large armor drop. Being as the only large races we had with us were barbs, they lucked out and got to roll on nearly everything. <P>I have to agree on the post above about not pouting. I've never won a roll on any raid we've been on and I lead them. *grin* It's just for fun and to help your friends get items they can use. But everyone who helped on the raid should be able to roll on the items they can use. I agree with that. But it also depends from server to server and guild to guild and leader to leader. everyone's got their own ideas about how to loot. There really is no "right" way to do it.<P><BR>Hope I helped,<P>Iceya Silvervein of Bloodsong<BR>35th lesson of enchantment<BR>Lanys T'Vyl server<P>------------------<BR>Drinking, fighting and trading breeze for a sow whenever possible.
</FONT>
